1
00:00:59,875 --> 00:01:02,615
[Episode 19: Exile Order]

2
00:01:08,206 --> 00:01:10,692
PD Shin.

3
00:01:10,692 --> 00:01:13,778
I figured you'd go to Writer Kim Ju Ho first.

4
00:01:13,778 --> 00:01:15,048
What are you doing here?

5
00:01:15,048 --> 00:01:17,671
I thought I should come to you first.

6
00:01:17,671 --> 00:01:19,273
What for?

7
00:01:20,941 --> 00:01:22,734
What brings you here?

8
00:01:25,258 --> 00:01:27,751
I'm curious too, Soon Rok.

9
00:01:27,751 --> 00:01:29,593
Why are we here?

10
00:01:29,593 --> 00:01:32,599
Why did we come here?

11
00:01:34,281 --> 00:01:35,456
I'm not sure.

12
00:01:35,456 --> 00:01:38,364
You don't know?

13
00:01:38,364 --> 00:01:39,798
I really don't.

14
00:01:39,798 --> 00:01:42,091
I can't explain it myself.

15
00:01:42,091 --> 00:01:44,965
What? You really don't know either?

16
00:01:44,965 --> 00:01:47,945
What is that even supposed to mean?

17
00:01:49,882 --> 00:01:53,000
Why did you blow off your date with Jenny?

18
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,040
I don't know.

19
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:56,936
You don't know that either?

20
00:01:58,183 --> 00:02:00,173
I shouldn't have done that.

21
00:02:00,173 --> 00:02:02,340
Get it together, Soon Rok.

22
00:02:02,340 --> 00:02:04,465
What are you even saying?

23
00:02:04,465 --> 00:02:07,260
Why is he acting like this?

24
00:02:07,260 --> 00:02:09,978
Exactly, you shouldn't do that.

25
00:02:10,798 --> 00:02:14,586
Is that what you're here to say sorry for?

26
00:02:16,272 --> 00:02:19,023
Don't worry about me, just go and...

27
00:02:19,023 --> 00:02:21,271
That's not why I'm here.

28
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:25,782
Then what?

29
00:02:25,782 --> 00:02:28,431
I think I might

30
00:02:32,405 --> 00:02:34,998
have feelings for you.

31
00:02:59,694 --> 00:03:00,708
Emergency!

32
00:03:00,708 --> 00:03:02,093
Emergency!

33
00:03:03,305 --> 00:03:04,618
Guys, it's an emergency!

34
00:03:04,618 --> 00:03:06,538
Emergency!

35
00:03:07,471 --> 00:03:09,762
He likes Yumi?

36
00:03:09,762 --> 00:03:11,553
Soon Rok just confessed!

37
00:03:11,553 --> 00:03:14,018
Soon Rok likes Yumi!

38
00:03:14,018 --> 00:03:16,583
Soon Rok likes Yumi?

39
00:03:16,583 --> 00:03:17,627
What?

40
00:03:17,627 --> 00:03:19,274
- Since when?
- Since when?

41
00:03:19,274 --> 00:03:21,535
He just confessed!

42
00:03:33,794 --> 00:03:35,107
Yeah?

43
00:03:36,803 --> 00:03:38,653
Wait, what do you mean...

44
00:03:38,653 --> 00:03:40,996
Who's at the door?

45
00:03:40,996 --> 00:03:43,082
PD Shin?

46
00:03:43,082 --> 00:03:45,628
Are you okay?

47
00:03:45,628 --> 00:03:47,472
- Are you hurt?
- No.

48
00:03:47,472 --> 00:03:50,097
No, I'm fine.

49
00:03:50,097 --> 00:03:53,668
Na Hui stayed too. She was worried.

50
00:03:53,668 --> 00:03:54,995
What happened to you?

51
00:03:54,995 --> 00:03:57,981
I was dying to know.

52
00:03:59,031 --> 00:04:00,389
I'm sorry.

53
00:04:00,389 --> 00:04:02,039
Why were you two fighting?

54
00:04:02,039 --> 00:04:04,002
We can talk about that later.

55
00:04:04,002 --> 00:04:06,167
You should go. The Editor's waiting.

56
00:04:06,167 --> 00:04:07,937
Right. I'll get going.

57
00:04:07,937 --> 00:04:10,764
- But you just got here...
- Just go.

58
00:04:10,764 --> 00:04:12,444
Okay, then...

59
00:04:16,094 --> 00:04:19,125
Why did he even come here?

60
00:04:19,125 --> 00:04:20,303
I don't know.

61
00:04:20,303 --> 00:04:22,710
Maybe he thought we'd worry.

62
00:04:22,710 --> 00:04:24,815
Na Hui, you should go now.

63
00:04:24,815 --> 00:04:26,188
It's late.

64
00:04:26,188 --> 00:04:28,268
It's not that late.

65
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:30,001
I'll go too. Let's go together.

66
00:04:30,001 --> 00:04:31,738
Grab your stuff.

67
00:04:36,599 --> 00:04:38,660
<i>The doors are closing.</i>

68
00:04:48,030 --> 00:04:49,696
This is insane.

69
00:04:50,746 --> 00:04:54,369
What's wrong with him today?

70
00:04:54,369 --> 00:04:56,500
Hey, say something.

71
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:59,013
Why did he suddenly confess?

72
00:04:59,013 --> 00:05:02,083
This is ridiculous.

73
00:05:02,083 --> 00:05:04,443
So, here's the thing.

74
00:05:04,443 --> 00:05:06,969
Take a look at this.

75
00:05:10,169 --> 00:05:11,792
What is that?

76
00:05:11,792 --> 00:05:13,458
We removed it, right?

77
00:05:13,458 --> 00:05:16,243
But it got bigger.

78
00:05:16,243 --> 00:05:17,430
Well...

79
00:05:17,430 --> 00:05:20,188
That's not Writer Yumi's photo.

80
00:05:20,188 --> 00:05:22,542
It's Soon Rok's.

81
00:05:22,542 --> 00:05:23,597
What?

82
00:05:23,597 --> 00:05:26,098
It used to be this small,

83
00:05:26,098 --> 00:05:27,998
but when I checked today...

84
00:05:27,998 --> 00:05:29,724
it got this big.

85
00:05:30,934 --> 00:05:34,007
Then why did you draw the line?

86
00:05:36,168 --> 00:05:37,949
I...

87
00:05:37,949 --> 00:05:40,329
misdiagnosed it.

88
00:05:40,329 --> 00:05:41,903
I'm sorry.

89
00:05:41,903 --> 00:05:44,707
I messed everything up.

90
00:05:44,707 --> 00:05:47,887
You think "sorry" fixes this?

91
00:05:49,238 --> 00:05:51,570
You quack!

92
00:05:51,570 --> 00:05:53,263
A total quack!

93
00:05:53,263 --> 00:05:55,724
Hey, where are you going?

94
00:05:55,724 --> 00:05:57,207
I'll fix this.

95
00:05:57,207 --> 00:05:59,158
Just wait.

96
00:05:59,158 --> 00:06:02,071
And what exactly are you going to fix?

97
00:06:06,455 --> 00:06:08,988
- Someone's coming!
- Who's there?

98
00:06:11,068 --> 00:06:13,708
Hey, guys.

99
00:06:17,233 --> 00:06:20,431
I'm Soon Rok's Love Cell.

100
00:06:20,431 --> 00:06:22,458
Love Cell?

101
00:06:22,458 --> 00:06:25,023
Can you open the door?

102
00:06:25,023 --> 00:06:28,989
I need to talk to Yumi's Love Cell.

103
00:06:30,738 --> 00:06:32,463
Soon Rok's Love Cell?

104
00:06:32,463 --> 00:06:35,764
<i>What do we do? Let him in or not?</i>

105
00:06:36,417 --> 00:06:38,067
He came all the way here?

106
00:06:38,067 --> 00:06:40,125
That's totally for real!

107
00:06:40,125 --> 00:06:42,538
That was a real confession.

108
00:06:43,378 --> 00:06:45,104
Oh my gosh!

109
00:06:56,943 --> 00:07:01,106
<i>There's one more thing
that's changed as I got older...</i>

110
00:07:01,106 --> 00:07:02,933
Open the door.

111
00:07:04,750 --> 00:07:06,208
Let's go see Love Cell!

112
00:07:06,208 --> 00:07:07,250
Hold on.

113
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:08,802
Stay out of this.

114
00:07:08,802 --> 00:07:10,256
Hey, let go!

115
00:07:10,256 --> 00:07:14,002
<i>I can feel my rational side
getting stronger too.</i>

116
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,008
Thanks.

117
00:07:17,008 --> 00:07:18,756
Grab him!

118
00:07:21,625 --> 00:07:24,125
What are you doing?

119
00:07:26,031 --> 00:07:29,423
Court is now in session.

120
00:07:30,185 --> 00:07:32,831
The defendant, Shin Soon Rok,
is charged as follows.

121
00:07:33,458 --> 00:07:34,499
First.

122
00:07:34,499 --> 00:07:36,358
From day one,

123
00:07:36,358 --> 00:07:39,789
you confused Yumi with your odd behavior

124
00:07:39,789 --> 00:07:41,958
and repeatedly disrupted her writing.

125
00:07:41,958 --> 00:07:43,014
Do you admit it?

126
00:07:43,014 --> 00:07:44,827
<i>Can we talk now?</i>

127
00:07:44,827 --> 00:07:46,594
<i>Do you not like working with me?</i>

128
00:07:46,594 --> 00:07:48,319
<i>- Okay, got it.
- Hey!</i>

129
00:07:48,319 --> 00:07:50,385
<i>- Yeah.
- Hey!</i>

130
00:07:52,561 --> 00:07:53,779
<i>Writer Kim!</i>

131
00:07:53,779 --> 00:07:55,595
<i>Writer Kim.</i>

132
00:07:59,457 --> 00:08:00,755
Well...

133
00:08:00,755 --> 00:08:02,915
I didn't mean to, but...

134
00:08:03,994 --> 00:08:06,306
if it made you uncomfortable,

135
00:08:06,306 --> 00:08:07,344
I'm sorry.

136
00:08:07,344 --> 00:08:09,405
So, do you admit it?

137
00:08:09,405 --> 00:08:12,120
I do.

138
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,959
Second.

139
00:08:14,789 --> 00:08:17,598
With pointless lovely smiles and cute charm,

140
00:08:17,598 --> 00:08:20,064
you made her heart flutter.

141
00:08:23,613 --> 00:08:26,311
- He was so cute.
- He was adorable.

142
00:08:26,311 --> 00:08:29,524
- I remember that.
- So adorable.

143
00:08:29,524 --> 00:08:31,035
Do you admit it?

144
00:08:31,035 --> 00:08:33,815
Well, that's just his natural charm...

145
00:08:33,815 --> 00:08:36,260
Do you admit it?

146
00:08:36,260 --> 00:08:37,693
I do.

147
00:08:37,693 --> 00:08:38,813
Third.

148
00:08:38,813 --> 00:08:40,708
You texted her to go see a movie.

149
00:08:40,708 --> 00:08:41,757
<i>You're cool.</i>

150
00:08:41,757 --> 00:08:44,479
You casually threw around compliments,

151
00:08:44,479 --> 00:08:46,296
showed up in the rain with an umbrella,

152
00:08:46,296 --> 00:08:49,862
and made her heart race for no good reason.

153
00:08:51,819 --> 00:08:55,089
Yeah... that day really got to me.

154
00:08:55,089 --> 00:08:57,152
Do you admit it?

155
00:08:58,418 --> 00:09:00,204
I do.

156
00:09:00,204 --> 00:09:01,451
Fourth.

157
00:09:01,451 --> 00:09:02,738
You gave her hope,

158
00:09:02,738 --> 00:09:06,378
then drew the line by asking for a blind date.

159
00:09:07,129 --> 00:09:09,762
<i>Do you know anyone I could meet?</i>

160
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:15,086
- Exactly.
- That was the worst.

161
00:09:16,151 --> 00:09:18,223
Do you admit it?

162
00:09:18,223 --> 00:09:19,484
I do.

163
00:09:19,484 --> 00:09:21,019
- Fifth.
- There's more?

164
00:09:21,019 --> 00:09:23,726
You even went on a blind date
with someone Yumi knows,

165
00:09:23,726 --> 00:09:26,366
then bailed and hurt Jenny.

166
00:09:26,366 --> 00:09:28,613
That was inconsiderate
to the person who set it up.

167
00:09:28,613 --> 00:09:29,886
Do you admit it?

168
00:09:29,886 --> 00:09:31,036
I do.

169
00:09:31,036 --> 00:09:33,107
That was completely my fault.

170
00:09:33,107 --> 00:09:34,590
But all of this happened because

171
00:09:34,590 --> 00:09:38,155
he didn't realize how he truly felt...

172
00:09:38,155 --> 00:09:39,281
Sixth.

173
00:09:39,281 --> 00:09:41,709
You suddenly confessed out of nowhere,

174
00:09:41,709 --> 00:09:44,496
throwing everything into chaos.

175
00:09:44,496 --> 00:09:47,042
Do you admit it?

176
00:09:47,042 --> 00:09:50,220
- Admit it.
- You have to.

177
00:09:50,220 --> 00:09:51,733
Come on!

178
00:09:53,179 --> 00:09:54,745
I do.

179
00:09:54,745 --> 00:09:57,158
The defendant admits all charges.

180
00:09:57,158 --> 00:10:00,285
Shin Soon Rok caused
upheaval in Yumi's Village,

181
00:10:00,285 --> 00:10:02,345
delayed her writing,

182
00:10:02,345 --> 00:10:06,082
and dealt serious damage to her relationships.

183
00:10:06,082 --> 00:10:07,723
Therefore...

184
00:10:07,723 --> 00:10:09,159
Verdict!

185
00:10:09,159 --> 00:10:11,905
Yumi will reject

186
00:10:13,715 --> 00:10:15,729
Shin Soon Rok's confession!

187
00:10:16,418 --> 00:10:19,336
- Reject it?
- Calm down.

188
00:10:20,647 --> 00:10:24,514
And to prevent further influence,

189
00:10:24,514 --> 00:10:28,194
he is hereby banished from Yumi's Village.

190
00:10:28,194 --> 00:10:31,024
Soon Rok is hereby

191
00:10:31,024 --> 00:10:32,683
banished from Yumi's Village!

192
00:10:42,657 --> 00:10:44,457
Are you okay?

193
00:10:45,111 --> 00:10:48,571
- Get out of here. Now!
- Get lost.

194
00:11:28,048 --> 00:11:30,046
<i>PD Shin,</i>

195
00:11:30,046 --> 00:11:33,584
<i>I'm going to pretend I didn't hear that.</i>

196
00:11:33,584 --> 00:11:36,381
<i>I didn't realize you could be this immature.</i>

197
00:11:36,381 --> 00:11:38,523
<i>That was very reckless.</i>

198
00:11:39,588 --> 00:11:41,994
<i>Please apologize to Writer Ju Ho,</i>

199
00:11:41,994 --> 00:11:44,759
<i>and handle the situation properly.</i>

200
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:32,630
Smells nice.

201
00:12:43,698 --> 00:12:45,324
Tastes good.

202
00:12:52,589 --> 00:12:55,474
She finally feels calm again.

203
00:12:55,474 --> 00:12:57,963
This is the real Yumi.

204
00:13:01,826 --> 00:13:04,555
This is how my mornings used to start...

205
00:13:04,555 --> 00:13:08,048
quietly planning what I'd write today.

206
00:13:09,246 --> 00:13:11,311
This feels peaceful.

207
00:13:14,628 --> 00:13:16,800
Soon Rok.

208
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:20,393
Soon Rok, it's already 11.

209
00:13:20,393 --> 00:13:21,558
<i>I know.</i>

210
00:13:21,558 --> 00:13:25,026
How long are you going to lie there?

211
00:13:26,554 --> 00:13:28,391
<i>I've got no energy.</i>

212
00:13:28,391 --> 00:13:30,373
<i>I can't get up.</i>

213
00:13:37,119 --> 00:13:39,168
Gosh...

214
00:13:39,168 --> 00:13:42,493
He's been lying around all day
and he's still not recharged.

215
00:13:42,493 --> 00:13:44,834
What should I do?

216
00:13:45,935 --> 00:13:49,636
You still have one thing left to do.

217
00:13:49,636 --> 00:13:52,358
You need to call Jenny.

218
00:13:56,130 --> 00:13:58,343
Come on, last bit of strength.

219
00:13:58,343 --> 00:14:01,756
Let's at least end this properly.

220
00:14:23,531 --> 00:14:25,048
<i>Jenny.</i>

221
00:14:25,048 --> 00:14:28,590
<i>I'm really sorry about yesterday.</i>

222
00:14:33,163 --> 00:14:36,255
<i>Honestly, I've been pretty busy lately...</i>

223
00:14:36,255 --> 00:14:38,102
[Ms. Jenny]

224
00:14:38,102 --> 00:14:39,889
It's Jenny.

225
00:14:44,322 --> 00:14:46,111
Hello?

226
00:14:46,838 --> 00:14:48,030
Yes, Jenny.

227
00:14:48,030 --> 00:14:50,339
Hello, are you busy?

228
00:14:50,339 --> 00:14:52,846
Can you talk for a minute?

229
00:14:52,846 --> 00:14:54,096
Yeah.

230
00:14:54,096 --> 00:14:56,982
I'm really sorry about yesterday.

231
00:15:10,095 --> 00:15:12,040
Hey, Jenny.

232
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:16,546
I meant to call, but it got too late.

233
00:15:16,546 --> 00:15:18,851
That must've been confusing yesterday, huh?

234
00:15:18,851 --> 00:15:20,037
Yeah.

235
00:15:20,037 --> 00:15:22,037
It was a little confusing.

236
00:15:22,037 --> 00:15:24,542
I think something urgent came up

237
00:15:24,542 --> 00:15:27,055
at the publishing company.

238
00:15:27,055 --> 00:15:29,713
I didn't get the full story,

239
00:15:29,713 --> 00:15:33,711
but I'll ask PD Shin at the meeting.

240
00:15:33,711 --> 00:15:36,758
I actually just spoke with Soon Rok.

241
00:15:36,758 --> 00:15:38,215
<i>Oh, really?</i>

242
00:15:38,215 --> 00:15:40,142
He sounded really sorry.

243
00:15:40,142 --> 00:15:41,459
He asked to meet today.

244
00:15:41,459 --> 00:15:43,335
Oh, you're meeting him?

245
00:15:43,335 --> 00:15:44,593
<i>No.</i>

246
00:15:44,593 --> 00:15:45,926
<i>Yumi,</i>

247
00:15:45,926 --> 00:15:48,095
<i>actually...</i>

248
00:15:49,619 --> 00:15:52,069
Jeong Sik

249
00:15:52,069 --> 00:15:54,736
suddenly reached out.

250
00:15:54,736 --> 00:15:58,207
Your ex-boyfriend?

251
00:15:58,207 --> 00:15:59,547
<i>Yeah.</i>

252
00:15:59,547 --> 00:16:02,578
<i>We broke up about two months ago,</i>

253
00:16:02,578 --> 00:16:05,909
<i>but he showed up last night.</i>

254
00:16:05,909 --> 00:16:08,516
So we...

255
00:16:08,516 --> 00:16:11,038
decided to get back together.

256
00:16:13,176 --> 00:16:14,354
Oh, okay.

257
00:16:14,354 --> 00:16:15,934
<i>I'm really sorry.</i>

258
00:16:15,934 --> 00:16:17,705
<i>This was so sudden.</i>

259
00:16:17,705 --> 00:16:19,812
No, it's okay.

260
00:16:19,812 --> 00:16:22,992
That's good for you.

261
00:16:22,992 --> 00:16:24,610
I'm glad.

262
00:16:24,610 --> 00:16:28,738
I felt like I should be honest with you.

263
00:16:30,388 --> 00:16:33,755
And Yumi didn't know,
so please don't misunderstand.

264
00:16:33,755 --> 00:16:35,148
Of course.

265
00:16:35,148 --> 00:16:36,695
I understand.

266
00:16:36,695 --> 00:16:39,421
<i>I'll tell her too.</i>

267
00:16:39,421 --> 00:16:41,123
Okay.

268
00:16:42,273 --> 00:16:43,371
I'm sorry.

269
00:16:43,371 --> 00:16:45,925
No, don't worry about it.

270
00:16:45,925 --> 00:16:47,478
Congratulations.

271
00:16:47,478 --> 00:16:50,422
I don't even know if "thank you" is right...

272
00:16:50,422 --> 00:16:53,062
That's good for you.

273
00:16:53,062 --> 00:16:55,255
I mean it.

274
00:17:01,220 --> 00:17:04,078
<i>I told him,</i>

275
00:17:04,078 --> 00:17:05,789
<i>but I feel so bad.</i>

276
00:17:05,789 --> 00:17:07,462
Well...

277
00:17:08,131 --> 00:17:10,222
I'm sure he understands.

278
00:17:10,222 --> 00:17:11,997
<i>I feel bad for you too.</i>

279
00:17:11,997 --> 00:17:13,850
Oh, no.

280
00:17:14,749 --> 00:17:16,373
Good for you.

281
00:17:16,373 --> 00:17:17,795
Congratulations.

282
00:17:22,085 --> 00:17:24,657
Call me when you're done with your deadline.

283
00:17:24,657 --> 00:17:26,297
Dinner's on me.

284
00:17:26,297 --> 00:17:28,062
Thank you so much.

285
00:17:28,062 --> 00:17:30,708
Yeah, see you later.

286
00:17:38,041 --> 00:17:40,319
What was that?

287
00:17:40,319 --> 00:17:42,941
If they were getting back together,
she could've done it a day earlier!

288
00:17:42,941 --> 00:17:45,796
Then Soon Rok wouldn't have been banished.

289
00:17:46,381 --> 00:17:49,000
Can't we go see him?

290
00:17:50,403 --> 00:17:51,958
It's over.

291
00:17:51,958 --> 00:17:53,020
Why?

292
00:17:53,020 --> 00:17:54,997
He likes Yumi,

293
00:17:54,997 --> 00:17:56,750
and Yumi liked him too!

294
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:59,981
They already ended things cleanly.

295
00:17:59,981 --> 00:18:01,921
Exactly.

296
00:18:01,921 --> 00:18:05,239
- It's over.
- What's done is done.

297
00:18:05,239 --> 00:18:07,252
What's done is done.

298
00:18:07,252 --> 00:18:09,850
Going back now would just mess with him.

299
00:18:09,850 --> 00:18:11,150
That's not right.

300
00:18:11,150 --> 00:18:12,875
Let's not do that.

301
00:18:12,875 --> 00:18:15,510
Hey, you guys are so...

302
00:18:16,746 --> 00:18:18,495
Where is she going?

303
00:18:27,458 --> 00:18:29,096
Cold, all of you.

304
00:18:29,096 --> 00:18:30,903
Feelings change.

305
00:18:30,903 --> 00:18:32,723
That's just how it works.

306
00:18:32,723 --> 00:18:35,889
Fine. If you won't do it, I will.

307
00:18:37,666 --> 00:18:39,979
Let's go, Yumi.

308
00:18:43,050 --> 00:18:44,742
Let's go

309
00:18:44,742 --> 00:18:46,262
to Soon Rok.

310
00:18:46,262 --> 00:18:48,169
Starting now...

311
00:18:48,169 --> 00:18:51,802
Heart Fever Time!

312
00:18:52,796 --> 00:18:54,188
<i>"Heart Fever Time" is</i>

313
00:18:54,188 --> 00:18:56,675
<i>a temporary emotional surge</i>

314
00:18:56,675 --> 00:18:59,661
<i>where you feel like you can do anything.</i>

315
00:19:03,231 --> 00:19:05,875
Heart Fever Time!

316
00:19:05,875 --> 00:19:07,749
Time!

317
00:19:07,749 --> 00:19:08,780
Time!

318
00:19:08,780 --> 00:19:11,263
Time!

319
00:19:11,263 --> 00:19:12,750
Hey, Emotion Cell.

320
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:15,164
Stop.

321
00:19:16,623 --> 00:19:17,708
Move.

322
00:19:17,708 --> 00:19:19,214
I'm good at this.

323
00:19:19,214 --> 00:19:21,288
Don't you remember Babi?

324
00:19:21,288 --> 00:19:22,826
Heart Fever Time

325
00:19:22,826 --> 00:19:25,474
has an age limit.

326
00:19:26,381 --> 00:19:29,047
Yumi can't use it anymore.

327
00:19:29,972 --> 00:19:31,523
<i>Heart Fever Time</i>

328
00:19:31,523 --> 00:19:34,243
<i>sadly has an age limit.</i>

329
00:19:34,243 --> 00:19:36,283
<i>By your mid-30s,</i>

330
00:19:36,283 --> 00:19:38,996
<i>the ability fades away.</i>

331
00:19:53,324 --> 00:19:54,706
<i>But,</i>

332
00:19:54,706 --> 00:19:59,044
<i>Heart Fever Time isn't something
only Yumi can use.</i>

333
00:20:03,780 --> 00:20:06,649
<i>Heart Fever Time has begun.</i>

334
00:20:10,448 --> 00:20:12,073
What is this?

335
00:20:15,677 --> 00:20:17,990
It's coming out of Emotion Cell's house!

336
00:20:23,708 --> 00:20:26,523
This is Heart Fever Time.

337
00:20:26,523 --> 00:20:28,156
Heart Fever Time?

338
00:20:28,156 --> 00:20:31,656
No way. I've only heard about this.

339
00:20:31,656 --> 00:20:34,389
Wow, first time seeing it in our village.

340
00:20:39,420 --> 00:20:41,208
Soon Rok, let's go.

341
00:20:41,208 --> 00:20:43,061
To Writer Kim... no.

342
00:20:43,061 --> 00:20:46,074
To Yumi noona!

343
00:21:13,694 --> 00:21:15,881
<i>Run, Soon Rok!</i>

344
00:21:18,320 --> 00:21:21,086
<i>- Run, Soon Rok!
- Run, Soon Rok!</i>

345
00:22:04,739 --> 00:22:07,220
<i>I guess she's not home.</i>

346
00:22:07,220 --> 00:22:08,797
<i>Maybe this is too much.</i>

347
00:22:08,797 --> 00:22:10,448
<i>She clearly rejected you...</i>

348
00:22:10,448 --> 00:22:13,137
<i>Why go back just to hear more?</i>

349
00:22:15,874 --> 00:22:18,680
<i>Think about it. How big is the age gap?</i>

350
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:21,626
<i>She doesn't even see you as a man.</i>

351
00:22:36,750 --> 00:22:38,108
<i>Let's go back.</i>

352
00:22:38,108 --> 00:22:41,030
<i>This isn't like you.</i>

353
00:23:06,296 --> 00:23:07,554
<i>Mr. Soon Rok,</i>

354
00:23:07,554 --> 00:23:10,288
<i>thank you for understanding and supporting me.</i>

355
00:23:10,288 --> 00:23:11,563
<i>Take care.</i>

356
00:23:11,563 --> 00:23:14,483
<i>Maybe we'll run into each other someday?</i>

357
00:23:17,732 --> 00:23:18,818
<i>Yeah.</i>

358
00:23:18,818 --> 00:23:21,060
<i>You take care too.</i>

359
00:23:27,304 --> 00:23:30,556
<i>Maybe we'll meet again at Yumi's wedding.</i>

360
00:23:30,556 --> 00:23:32,716
<i>Whenever that may be...</i>

361
00:23:34,006 --> 00:23:36,061
<i>"Wedding?"</i>

362
00:23:39,489 --> 00:23:41,576
<i>Come on, hurry up!</i>

363
00:23:47,807 --> 00:23:50,313
<i>PD Shin, over here.</i>

364
00:23:51,609 --> 00:23:53,663
<i>Hurry!</i>

365
00:24:04,210 --> 00:24:06,323
<i>Oh, he's my coworker.</i>

366
00:24:09,126 --> 00:24:10,546
<i>Mr. Soon Rok?</i>

367
00:24:10,546 --> 00:24:13,055
<i>Hi. It's been a while.</i>

368
00:24:17,882 --> 00:24:19,253
<i>Come take a picture with us.</i>

369
00:24:19,253 --> 00:24:21,310
No, no.

370
00:24:21,310 --> 00:24:23,476
I can't even imagine that.

371
00:24:24,726 --> 00:24:27,657
Come on, one more push!

372
00:24:27,657 --> 00:24:31,281
Heart Fever Time!

373
00:24:57,747 --> 00:25:00,083
<i>Run, Soon Rok!</i>

374
00:25:00,083 --> 00:25:02,634
<i>- Run, Soon Rok!
- Run, Soon Rok!</i>

375
00:25:18,955 --> 00:25:20,675
Hello.

376
00:26:04,014 --> 00:26:05,804
Who is it?

377
00:26:05,804 --> 00:26:07,198
Writer Kim,

378
00:26:07,198 --> 00:26:09,370
it's me. Soon Rok.

379
00:26:10,233 --> 00:26:14,186
<i>Haven't we seen this before?</i>

380
00:26:19,423 --> 00:26:21,116
PD Shin?

381
00:26:21,116 --> 00:26:24,873
<i>Yeah, this is exactly like yesterday.</i>

382
00:26:26,352 --> 00:26:28,424
What brings you here?

383
00:26:28,424 --> 00:26:32,550
<i>It's the same as yesterday. Darn it.</i>

384
00:26:33,136 --> 00:26:35,311
You didn't even call.

385
00:26:35,311 --> 00:26:37,806
Why are you here?

386
00:26:43,477 --> 00:26:44,951
Yeah?

387
00:26:49,651 --> 00:26:51,608
Don't tell me

388
00:26:51,608 --> 00:26:53,739
you don't know again.

389
00:26:53,739 --> 00:26:56,341
- What on earth...
- Well...

390
00:27:01,262 --> 00:27:04,273
Everything you said is right.

391
00:27:04,273 --> 00:27:07,433
I was being immature.

392
00:27:08,641 --> 00:27:11,073
And reckless.

393
00:27:12,128 --> 00:27:14,236
I admit that.

394
00:27:15,901 --> 00:27:18,201
This is ridiculous.

395
00:27:18,201 --> 00:27:21,547
Showing up like this out of nowhere...

396
00:27:25,228 --> 00:27:27,549
But...

397
00:27:27,549 --> 00:27:29,498
still...

398
00:27:35,422 --> 00:27:37,876
No matter how I think about it,

399
00:27:40,316 --> 00:27:42,575
I like you, Writer Kim.

400
00:27:43,602 --> 00:27:46,368
It's pathetic I only realized now,

401
00:27:48,185 --> 00:27:50,498
but I think

402
00:27:52,109 --> 00:27:54,645
I've liked you from the start.

403
00:28:16,742 --> 00:28:18,703
Yesterday,

404
00:28:20,260 --> 00:28:22,128
you said it.

405
00:28:24,717 --> 00:28:26,381
Yes.

406
00:28:26,381 --> 00:28:28,174
And

407
00:28:28,758 --> 00:28:31,151
I rejected you.

408
00:28:32,279 --> 00:28:33,403
Yes.

409
00:28:33,403 --> 00:28:35,531
But now

410
00:28:37,365 --> 00:28:39,584
you're saying the same thing again.

411
00:28:41,779 --> 00:28:43,369
Yes.

412
00:28:49,636 --> 00:28:52,096
I think I'd regret it if I didn't.

413
00:28:59,665 --> 00:29:01,572
No answer...

414
00:29:02,161 --> 00:29:04,732
Did he just get rejected again?

415
00:29:05,924 --> 00:29:08,202
Let's go.

416
00:29:08,202 --> 00:29:10,394
Rejected twice in a row...

417
00:29:10,394 --> 00:29:12,967
He's never felt this humiliated before.

418
00:29:21,761 --> 00:29:23,358
By the way...

419
00:29:24,265 --> 00:29:26,463
Have you had lunch?

420
00:29:29,496 --> 00:29:31,387
No.

421
00:29:31,387 --> 00:29:34,313
Do you want to eat together?

422
00:29:38,586 --> 00:29:41,081
[Episode 20: Welcome to my home]

423
00:29:51,103 --> 00:29:53,138
The door opened!

424
00:29:57,287 --> 00:29:59,215
It's open.

425
00:30:11,015 --> 00:30:12,685
He's back again.

426
00:30:12,685 --> 00:30:14,885
He got kicked out and still came back.

427
00:30:14,885 --> 00:30:16,620
Bold move.

428
00:30:16,620 --> 00:30:18,713
What if he gets kicked out again?

429
00:30:18,713 --> 00:30:20,904
You got this!

430
00:30:20,904 --> 00:30:22,631
- Welcome, Soon Rok.
- Go for it.

431
00:30:22,631 --> 00:30:24,250
Welcome, Soon Rok.

432
00:30:24,250 --> 00:30:25,494
Hang in there.

433
00:30:25,494 --> 00:30:26,891
Thanks.

434
00:30:27,854 --> 00:30:31,558
I came to see Yumi's Love Cell.

435
00:30:31,558 --> 00:30:34,756
Go that way if you want to find her.

436
00:30:34,756 --> 00:30:37,223
- Okay.
- We're rooting for you.

437
00:30:37,223 --> 00:30:39,383
Thanks!

438
00:30:55,437 --> 00:30:56,656
Hey.

439
00:30:56,656 --> 00:30:59,181
Oh, so you're Love Cell.

440
00:30:59,181 --> 00:31:01,574
Writer Kim really is on another level.

441
00:31:01,574 --> 00:31:03,979
No wonder she writes such great romance,

442
00:31:03,979 --> 00:31:06,245
with a Love Cell this huge.

443
00:31:06,245 --> 00:31:09,337
Wait, I'm not Love Cell. I'm Hungry Cell.

444
00:31:09,337 --> 00:31:10,369
What?

445
00:31:10,369 --> 00:31:13,347
Love Cell lives over there. Try that way.

446
00:31:13,347 --> 00:31:15,180
Oh, really?

447
00:31:15,180 --> 00:31:16,860
Thanks.

448
00:31:18,024 --> 00:31:19,133
Wait.

449
00:31:19,133 --> 00:31:21,511
Have you had lunch?

450
00:31:21,511 --> 00:31:22,904
Lunch?

451
00:31:22,904 --> 00:31:26,624
Love is great, but you still need to eat.

452
00:31:28,193 --> 00:31:30,567
Have you had lunch?

453
00:31:31,297 --> 00:31:33,371
- No.
- Do you want...

454
00:31:33,371 --> 00:31:35,371
to eat together?

455
00:31:36,549 --> 00:31:38,477
Come in.

456
00:31:52,693 --> 00:31:55,726
I was just about to have lunch.

457
00:31:58,009 --> 00:32:00,810
Do you like naengmyeon?

458
00:32:01,433 --> 00:32:03,946
I was going to make bibim naengmyeon.

459
00:32:06,019 --> 00:32:08,306
- Hey.
- Yeah?

460
00:32:08,306 --> 00:32:11,235
Is bibim naengmyeon okay?

461
00:32:12,878 --> 00:32:14,811
Yes, yes.

462
00:32:14,811 --> 00:32:16,566
That sounds great.

463
00:32:20,332 --> 00:32:22,151
Have a seat.

464
00:32:44,529 --> 00:32:45,595
Hello.

465
00:32:45,595 --> 00:32:47,625
Is Love Cell around here?

466
00:32:47,625 --> 00:32:50,375
Are you Soon Rok's Love Cell?

467
00:32:50,375 --> 00:32:51,561
Nice to meet you.

468
00:32:51,561 --> 00:32:53,169
I'll be coming by often.

469
00:32:53,169 --> 00:32:54,980
"Often?"

470
00:32:54,980 --> 00:32:56,666
You were banished.

471
00:32:56,666 --> 00:32:58,979
Do you really have the right?

472
00:33:00,879 --> 00:33:03,463
You can eat two servings, right?

473
00:33:03,463 --> 00:33:05,823
Then I should make four.

474
00:33:05,823 --> 00:33:07,776
Four?

475
00:33:09,245 --> 00:33:11,608
There are three of us.

476
00:33:11,608 --> 00:33:13,653
Why isn't she coming out?

477
00:33:13,653 --> 00:33:16,346
Na Hui, PD Shin's here.

478
00:33:16,346 --> 00:33:18,904
Wait, what? Na Hui is here too?

479
00:33:18,904 --> 00:33:21,504
So this just means lunch and that's it?

480
00:33:21,504 --> 00:33:23,363
Was I just overthinking...

481
00:33:23,363 --> 00:33:25,589
We don't have a meeting today, right?

482
00:33:25,589 --> 00:33:27,527
Just

483
00:33:27,527 --> 00:33:29,260
kidding.

484
00:33:33,399 --> 00:33:35,171
It's just me.

485
00:33:35,171 --> 00:33:37,606
One serving isn't enough for me.

486
00:33:42,284 --> 00:33:44,940
Get it together!

487
00:33:44,940 --> 00:33:48,386
You looked so nervous, I was just teasing you.

488
00:33:51,128 --> 00:33:53,135
Be my guest.

489
00:34:03,977 --> 00:34:06,464
Good thing I at least have eggs.

490
00:34:17,332 --> 00:34:19,138
By the way...

491
00:34:21,713 --> 00:34:23,858
Are we just

492
00:34:23,858 --> 00:34:26,083
having naengmyeon?

493
00:34:26,083 --> 00:34:27,111
Sorry?

494
00:34:27,111 --> 00:34:30,329
You mean just that?

495
00:34:30,329 --> 00:34:32,281
It might not be enough.

496
00:34:32,281 --> 00:34:36,346
It'd be nice to grill some meat,
but I don't have any.

497
00:34:36,346 --> 00:34:39,852
- Should we just go out to eat?
- No.

498
00:34:39,852 --> 00:34:42,078
That's not what I meant.

499
00:34:45,289 --> 00:34:48,383
I didn't hear your answer.

500
00:34:51,074 --> 00:34:54,487
You didn't say anything.

501
00:35:02,254 --> 00:35:03,781
Yeah?

502
00:35:08,885 --> 00:35:10,763
I asked

503
00:35:10,763 --> 00:35:13,511
if you wanted to have lunch together.

504
00:35:15,038 --> 00:35:18,865
That's why I'm boiling water.

505
00:35:21,427 --> 00:35:24,468
Is that... your answer?

506
00:35:45,062 --> 00:35:46,879
Is this the place?

507
00:36:10,918 --> 00:36:14,356
Hi. I'm Soon Rok's Love Cell.

508
00:36:14,356 --> 00:36:17,042
I came because I have something to say.

509
00:36:19,010 --> 00:36:21,016
I've been waiting for you.

510
00:36:22,229 --> 00:36:24,234
Thanks for coming back.

511
00:36:24,234 --> 00:36:27,034
I didn't think I'd get another chance.

512
00:36:29,912 --> 00:36:31,996
Welcome.

513
00:36:32,847 --> 00:36:34,664
Nice to meet you.

514
00:36:45,158 --> 00:36:46,771
PD Shin.

515
00:36:47,680 --> 00:36:50,953
I like you too.

516
00:36:53,746 --> 00:36:55,838
From now on,

517
00:36:55,838 --> 00:36:58,159
let's make this work.

518
00:37:06,741 --> 00:37:08,767
Is that a good enough answer?

519
00:37:16,354 --> 00:37:18,004
Yes.

520
00:38:14,474 --> 00:38:15,858
Want me to help?

521
00:38:15,858 --> 00:38:17,384
No, just sit.

522
00:38:17,384 --> 00:38:20,510
Or grab a drink. There's plenty in the fridge.

523
00:38:25,900 --> 00:38:28,240
Do you like bibim naengmyeon?

524
00:38:29,914 --> 00:38:32,206
I prefer bibim over mul naengmyeon.

525
00:38:32,206 --> 00:38:33,600
What about you?

526
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:36,018
Same here.

527
00:38:36,018 --> 00:38:37,547
Good.

528
00:38:38,357 --> 00:38:40,495
Want egg garnish too?

529
00:38:40,495 --> 00:38:45,389
I like that better than boiled eggs.

530
00:38:46,657 --> 00:38:49,166
Then I'll do that.

531
00:38:49,166 --> 00:38:51,633
No, it's fine. Just sit.

532
00:38:51,633 --> 00:38:53,130
I'm really good at this.

533
00:38:53,130 --> 00:38:54,859
I'll do it.

534
00:38:56,984 --> 00:38:59,373
Put the shells here.

535
00:38:59,373 --> 00:39:01,693
Yes, noona.

536
00:39:09,949 --> 00:39:12,195
Is it a little weird if I call you noona?

537
00:39:12,195 --> 00:39:15,775
It feels strange to keep saying "Writer Kim."

538
00:39:17,082 --> 00:39:18,794
No, it's fine.

539
00:39:19,379 --> 00:39:21,755
Do you not like it?

540
00:39:21,755 --> 00:39:23,416
No.

541
00:39:23,416 --> 00:39:25,173
Noona.

542
00:39:25,173 --> 00:39:27,216
I like how that sounds.

543
00:39:27,216 --> 00:39:29,092
Yeah.

544
00:39:29,092 --> 00:39:31,308
You can drop the formal speech too.

545
00:39:32,568 --> 00:39:34,266
Oh, should I?

546
00:39:37,428 --> 00:39:39,131
Okay, I will...

547
00:39:39,131 --> 00:39:40,405
No.

548
00:39:40,405 --> 00:39:43,315
I'll ease into it.

549
00:39:43,315 --> 00:39:45,016
Okay.

550
00:39:45,016 --> 00:39:48,529
"Noona" lit the fuse.

551
00:39:50,268 --> 00:39:52,753
"Noo..."

552
00:39:52,753 --> 00:39:55,366
"Na."

553
00:39:56,958 --> 00:39:58,725
[Noona]

554
00:40:00,180 --> 00:40:03,867
Hello, everyone.
A new semester has finally begun.

555
00:40:06,268 --> 00:40:10,213
It's been a while
since I've been back teaching.

556
00:40:10,213 --> 00:40:14,417
Didn't think I'd see this day again.

557
00:40:14,417 --> 00:40:15,851
The new cells probably

558
00:40:15,851 --> 00:40:18,603
didn't even know I was here.

559
00:40:18,603 --> 00:40:20,289
- We didn't!
- We didn't!

560
00:40:21,254 --> 00:40:22,935
This semester,

561
00:40:22,935 --> 00:40:26,125
we're covering dating a younger guy.

562
00:40:26,125 --> 00:40:28,700
It may feel new,

563
00:40:28,700 --> 00:40:29,739
but keep up!

564
00:40:29,739 --> 00:40:32,554
We're moving fast this term.

565
00:40:32,554 --> 00:40:34,043
Stay with me.

566
00:40:34,043 --> 00:40:36,256
- Got it?
- Yes!

567
00:40:50,264 --> 00:40:52,364
Noona.

568
00:40:53,207 --> 00:40:56,763
Have you ever dated someone younger?

569
00:40:57,997 --> 00:40:59,198
No.

570
00:40:59,198 --> 00:41:01,451
What about you?

571
00:41:01,451 --> 00:41:04,322
Have you dated someone older?

572
00:41:04,322 --> 00:41:07,075
No. This is my first time.

573
00:41:11,680 --> 00:41:15,200
What about dating a coworker?

574
00:41:18,629 --> 00:41:20,279
What about you?

575
00:41:20,279 --> 00:41:21,759
First time.

576
00:41:21,759 --> 00:41:23,305
You?

577
00:41:24,791 --> 00:41:26,772
Once.

578
00:41:28,671 --> 00:41:32,969
How was it at work?

579
00:41:32,969 --> 00:41:34,456
Well...

580
00:41:34,456 --> 00:41:36,274
It didn't last long.

581
00:41:36,274 --> 00:41:38,927
I quit not long after.

582
00:41:38,927 --> 00:41:41,705
- Did anyone at work know?
- No.

583
00:41:41,705 --> 00:41:43,633
When was that?

584
00:41:45,544 --> 00:41:48,403
Before I debuted as a writer.

585
00:41:49,109 --> 00:41:53,718
By the way, were you always this curious?

586
00:41:53,718 --> 00:41:55,691
I'm just curious.

587
00:41:59,741 --> 00:42:01,583
Careful.

588
00:42:01,583 --> 00:42:03,666
Some sesame oil...

589
00:42:21,652 --> 00:42:23,363
That looks good.

590
00:42:27,122 --> 00:42:28,678
Given the mood,

591
00:42:28,678 --> 00:42:30,661
we can move things forward.

592
00:42:30,661 --> 00:42:33,408
Today's goal.

593
00:42:33,408 --> 00:42:35,108
Chapter one.

594
00:42:35,108 --> 00:42:37,761
Linking arms.

595
00:42:37,761 --> 00:42:38,879
Naughty Cell.

596
00:42:38,879 --> 00:42:40,570
It's their first day. Let's not rush.

597
00:42:40,570 --> 00:42:41,803
Don't mess this up again.

598
00:42:41,803 --> 00:42:43,348
What are you talking about?

599
00:42:43,348 --> 00:42:45,581
You have to consider Soon Rok's personality.

600
00:42:45,581 --> 00:42:48,640
He's not like her exes.

601
00:42:52,084 --> 00:42:55,170
We should be careful on workdays.

602
00:42:57,760 --> 00:42:59,941
Yeah, definitely.

603
00:42:59,941 --> 00:43:04,960
I'm already on thin ice with the Editor.

604
00:43:04,960 --> 00:43:06,277
Right.

605
00:43:06,277 --> 00:43:08,282
See? That's exactly what I mean.

606
00:43:08,282 --> 00:43:09,599
Holding hands,

607
00:43:09,599 --> 00:43:11,355
interlacing fingers,

608
00:43:11,355 --> 00:43:12,950
or putting an arm around you...

609
00:43:12,950 --> 00:43:15,795
[Julie Publishing]
Within one kilometer of the office,

610
00:43:15,795 --> 00:43:17,923
we should avoid all that.

611
00:43:21,781 --> 00:43:24,779
Teacher, the other class is way ahead.

612
00:43:24,779 --> 00:43:27,377
They're doing Chapters 1, 2, and 3 all at once.

613
00:43:27,377 --> 00:43:30,629
Gosh, our teacher is so old-school.

614
00:43:30,629 --> 00:43:33,223
Quiet! Put some respect on Yumi.

615
00:43:33,223 --> 00:43:34,629
You don't know anything.

616
00:43:35,518 --> 00:43:37,096
The studio too.

617
00:43:37,096 --> 00:43:39,316
Same one-kilometer rule.

618
00:43:39,316 --> 00:43:41,094
Absolutely no exceptions.

619
00:43:41,094 --> 00:43:42,885
No physical contact.

620
00:43:43,473 --> 00:43:45,107
Right.

621
00:43:46,536 --> 00:43:48,223
That's better.

622
00:43:50,884 --> 00:43:52,342
All done.

623
00:43:52,342 --> 00:43:54,238
Looks good.

624
00:44:01,746 --> 00:44:03,529
Wait.

625
00:44:07,123 --> 00:44:09,139
I forgot this.

626
00:44:15,193 --> 00:44:16,304
Master.

627
00:44:16,304 --> 00:44:18,059
Did you call for me?

628
00:44:39,376 --> 00:44:40,935
I'm here.

629
00:44:40,935 --> 00:44:43,229
[Naughty Cell]

630
00:44:43,229 --> 00:44:44,480
No.

631
00:44:44,480 --> 00:44:46,713
I didn't call you.

632
00:44:46,713 --> 00:44:47,760
You did.

633
00:44:47,760 --> 00:44:50,484
I'm sure you did.

634
00:44:50,484 --> 00:44:51,918
Dear Soon Rok

635
00:44:51,918 --> 00:44:54,617
was definitely looking for me.

636
00:45:10,408 --> 00:45:12,291
Let's eat.

637
00:45:13,034 --> 00:45:15,271
Can I ask you something?

638
00:45:20,470 --> 00:45:22,548
When you're dating,

639
00:45:23,436 --> 00:45:25,978
how long does it usually take before you kiss?

640
00:45:34,885 --> 00:45:36,831
Is it okay

641
00:45:37,923 --> 00:45:39,858
on the first day?

642
00:46:24,870 --> 00:46:26,683
But

643
00:46:27,707 --> 00:46:31,093
this is the studio.

644
00:46:32,698 --> 00:46:33,740
Sorry?

645
00:46:33,740 --> 00:46:36,246
You said no physical contact

646
00:46:36,246 --> 00:46:38,646
within one kilometer.

647
00:46:39,908 --> 00:46:43,447
It's the weekend.

648
00:46:44,752 --> 00:46:46,537
Oh, right.

649
00:46:46,537 --> 00:46:48,766
So it's fine.

650
00:47:17,363 --> 00:47:22,703
[Episode 21: Everything About My Boyfriend]

651
00:47:31,635 --> 00:47:34,118
Soon Rok, I'm here.

652
00:47:34,729 --> 00:47:36,667
- You're here?
- Wow...

653
00:47:36,667 --> 00:47:38,874
Feels kind of weird seeing you here.

654
00:47:38,874 --> 00:47:39,941
Writer Kim,

655
00:47:39,941 --> 00:47:44,054
the meeting with the editor isn't over yet,
so you'll need to wait a bit.

656
00:47:44,054 --> 00:47:47,567
Would about 30 minutes be okay?

657
00:47:47,567 --> 00:47:50,347
What? Why are you being so formal?

658
00:47:51,133 --> 00:47:52,774
Noona.

659
00:47:53,779 --> 00:47:55,491
We're at work.

660
00:47:55,491 --> 00:47:58,337
Didn't we agree to keep things low-key?

661
00:47:58,337 --> 00:48:00,435
I'm already on thin ice here.

662
00:48:00,435 --> 00:48:03,068
- If we're too obvious...
- But...

663
00:48:03,068 --> 00:48:06,019
you're the one standing out more right now.

664
00:48:12,858 --> 00:48:15,449
Please go on in, Writer Kim.

665
00:48:15,449 --> 00:48:17,056
Yes.

666
00:48:26,723 --> 00:48:29,211
- Hello, Writer Kim.
- Hello.

667
00:48:29,211 --> 00:48:30,982
Oh, did you change your hair?

668
00:48:30,982 --> 00:48:32,889
- It looks great.
- Oh, really?

669
00:48:32,889 --> 00:48:34,894
Thank you.

670
00:48:34,894 --> 00:48:35,964
This way,

671
00:48:35,964 --> 00:48:37,009
please.

672
00:48:37,632 --> 00:48:39,180
Yes.

673
00:48:43,636 --> 00:48:46,012
Would you sit over there?

674
00:48:46,012 --> 00:48:47,722
Yes.

675
00:48:52,423 --> 00:48:55,314
I printed the draft in advance.

676
00:48:55,314 --> 00:48:57,965
You might want to review it
before the editor arrives.

677
00:48:57,965 --> 00:48:59,585
Yes.

678
00:49:01,136 --> 00:49:03,617
Just mark anything you're unsure about.

679
00:49:03,617 --> 00:49:04,973
Yes.

680
00:49:13,831 --> 00:49:16,206
Would you like some coffee?

681
00:49:17,811 --> 00:49:18,917
Yes.

682
00:49:18,917 --> 00:49:19,956
"Yes."

683
00:49:19,956 --> 00:49:22,796
Can you stop saying that?

684
00:49:25,082 --> 00:49:28,228
You said to keep it low-key.

685
00:49:29,423 --> 00:49:31,441
I'll get you an iced Americano.

686
00:49:31,441 --> 00:49:33,056
By the way...

687
00:49:33,684 --> 00:49:36,076
am I still "noona?"

688
00:49:36,076 --> 00:49:37,156
You are.

689
00:49:37,156 --> 00:49:39,461
Calling me that

690
00:49:39,461 --> 00:49:43,306
makes me sound old.

691
00:49:43,306 --> 00:49:45,177
Why? I like it.

692
00:49:45,177 --> 00:49:46,970
Well...

693
00:49:47,928 --> 00:49:51,613
if you like it, you can keep calling me that.

694
00:49:51,613 --> 00:49:52,921
Excuse me.

695
00:49:52,921 --> 00:49:54,654
Otherwise, I'll organize

696
00:49:54,654 --> 00:49:58,947
the naming issue
and send feedback later this week.

697
00:49:58,947 --> 00:50:02,381
Sure. Send it by email. I'll review it.

698
00:50:06,179 --> 00:50:07,861
By the way, PD Shin,

699
00:50:07,861 --> 00:50:09,448
I have a question.

700
00:50:09,448 --> 00:50:12,374
- You can just mark that...
- Well...

701
00:50:13,166 --> 00:50:16,175
What exactly do you like about me?

702
00:50:16,175 --> 00:50:18,001
- Sorry?
- Tell me.

703
00:50:18,001 --> 00:50:21,441
What made you like me?

704
00:50:24,190 --> 00:50:26,476
Obviously...

705
00:50:28,534 --> 00:50:32,506
I like your writing style.
It's clean and straightforward.

706
00:50:32,506 --> 00:50:35,339
Sorry, I grabbed the wrong one.

707
00:50:36,538 --> 00:50:39,071
"Clean and straightforward."

708
00:50:43,883 --> 00:50:46,888
We're at work. Let's talk later.

709
00:50:50,885 --> 00:50:53,184
Tell me now.

710
00:50:56,171 --> 00:50:58,453
I'm curious.

711
00:50:58,453 --> 00:51:00,806
Why do you like me?

712
00:51:03,526 --> 00:51:05,325
Noona?

713
00:51:06,914 --> 00:51:08,682
Because you're pretty.

714
00:51:15,865 --> 00:51:17,676
"Pretty?"

715
00:51:17,676 --> 00:51:19,656
Oh, hello.

716
00:51:24,346 --> 00:51:26,060
Pretty?

717
00:51:26,060 --> 00:51:27,886
Yeah?

718
00:51:27,886 --> 00:51:30,680
Am I extra pretty today?

719
00:51:30,680 --> 00:51:32,205
<i>Dating someone Gen Z...</i>

720
00:51:32,205 --> 00:51:35,071
<i>nothing goes as expected.</i>

721
00:51:40,373 --> 00:51:43,763
<i>What time do you get off? Want to grab dinner?</i>

722
00:51:57,199 --> 00:51:58,778
<i>I can't do dinner tonight.</i>

723
00:51:58,778 --> 00:52:01,639
<i>It's my laundry and cleaning day.</i>

724
00:52:02,287 --> 00:52:03,906
What?

725
00:52:13,206 --> 00:52:16,160
<i>Do you really have to do that today?</i>

726
00:52:18,805 --> 00:52:20,370
<i>Yeah.</i>

727
00:52:20,370 --> 00:52:23,323
<i>Wednesdays are for chores.</i>

728
00:52:23,323 --> 00:52:24,876
What?

729
00:52:26,622 --> 00:52:27,940
Housekeeping Cell,

730
00:52:27,940 --> 00:52:29,366
does that make any sense to you?

731
00:52:29,366 --> 00:52:31,266
He's out of his mind.

732
00:52:32,280 --> 00:52:33,975
And that lunatic is

733
00:52:33,975 --> 00:52:36,560
Yumi's boyfriend!

734
00:52:37,712 --> 00:52:40,981
Do Gen Z really care more about
routines than dating?

735
00:52:40,981 --> 00:52:44,287
It's only been a few days
and he's already like this?

736
00:52:54,463 --> 00:52:55,694
<i>Noona,</i>

737
00:52:55,694 --> 00:52:57,589
<i>come over at nine.</i>

738
00:52:59,341 --> 00:53:01,286
Where?

739
00:53:02,193 --> 00:53:03,947
<i>Where?</i>

740
00:53:09,470 --> 00:53:11,104
My place.

741
00:53:11,839 --> 00:53:15,052
I'll have everything cleaned up.

742
00:53:20,656 --> 00:53:21,746
Teacher,

743
00:53:21,746 --> 00:53:23,404
he told her to come over.

744
00:53:23,404 --> 00:53:25,417
Wait, hold on.

745
00:53:25,417 --> 00:53:27,375
He wants her over tonight?

746
00:53:27,375 --> 00:53:29,542
That's way too fast.

747
00:53:29,542 --> 00:53:31,773
What chapter is that again?

748
00:53:31,773 --> 00:53:35,118
Going over to her boyfriend's place
is Chapter 13.

749
00:53:35,118 --> 00:53:37,416
Wait, hang on.

750
00:53:37,416 --> 00:53:40,667
Well... where are we right now?

751
00:53:40,667 --> 00:53:41,732
Linking arms,

752
00:53:41,732 --> 00:53:42,833
holding hands,

753
00:53:42,833 --> 00:53:43,898
arm around the waist,

754
00:53:43,898 --> 00:53:45,367
hugging,

755
00:53:45,367 --> 00:53:48,919
and even the first kiss, all on day one.

756
00:53:48,919 --> 00:53:51,412
Right. We cleared up to Chapter 5.

757
00:53:51,412 --> 00:53:53,375
- Exactly.
- Teacher.

758
00:53:53,375 --> 00:53:55,863
If we jump from 5 to 13,

759
00:53:55,863 --> 00:53:58,241
when do we cover 6 through 12?

760
00:53:58,241 --> 00:54:00,841
Teacher, this syllabus is a mess.

761
00:54:00,841 --> 00:54:04,371
Teacher, what chapter are we on today?

762
00:54:04,371 --> 00:54:06,149
Enough!

763
00:54:06,149 --> 00:54:08,522
Quiet down!

764
00:54:09,220 --> 00:54:11,016
Just wait.

765
00:54:12,350 --> 00:54:13,583
Rational Cell!

766
00:54:13,583 --> 00:54:15,902
Change the textbook.

767
00:54:17,808 --> 00:54:19,801
It's outdated.

768
00:54:19,801 --> 00:54:22,894
Totally unrealistic!

769
00:54:31,227 --> 00:54:32,327
<i>Is it okay if I go?</i>

770
00:54:32,327 --> 00:54:34,677
<i>It feels kind of late.</i>

771
00:54:38,609 --> 00:54:40,619
<i>It's a holiday tomorrow.</i>

772
00:54:40,619 --> 00:54:43,115
<i>Let's hang out.</i>

773
00:54:43,115 --> 00:54:44,148
"Hang out?"

774
00:54:44,148 --> 00:54:46,741
What does that even mean?

775
00:54:55,006 --> 00:54:58,924
Dating someone Gen Z...
I seriously never know what to expect.

776
00:54:58,924 --> 00:55:01,296
Should I really go over to his place?

777
00:55:02,450 --> 00:55:05,043
PD Shin, here are the documents you asked for.

778
00:55:26,429 --> 00:55:28,929
- Noona.
- Soon Rok, I'm here.

779
00:55:28,929 --> 00:55:30,729
Come in.

780
00:55:32,702 --> 00:55:35,709
- You didn't have to bring anything.
- It's my first time here.

781
00:55:36,500 --> 00:55:37,805
Nice place.

782
00:55:37,805 --> 00:55:39,484
This way.

783
00:55:40,299 --> 00:55:42,139
What's this?

784
00:55:45,303 --> 00:55:46,408
Remember this?

785
00:55:46,408 --> 00:55:48,723
You can play now too.

786
00:55:48,723 --> 00:55:51,403
It's way more fun with two people.

787
00:55:52,083 --> 00:55:54,529
Hang on, I need to tweak the settings.

788
00:55:54,529 --> 00:55:57,595
So this is what you meant by "hang out?"

789
00:55:57,595 --> 00:55:59,053
Sorry?

790
00:55:59,053 --> 00:56:00,759
Nothing.

791
00:56:03,488 --> 00:56:05,153
Can I look around?

792
00:56:05,153 --> 00:56:06,623
Of course.

793
00:56:08,690 --> 00:56:10,277
Oh, careful.

794
00:56:11,862 --> 00:56:15,734
Games, comics, home workouts...

795
00:56:15,734 --> 00:56:18,005
So you're a homebody.

796
00:56:18,005 --> 00:56:20,225
I stay busy all night.

797
00:56:20,225 --> 00:56:21,667
What's this?

798
00:56:21,667 --> 00:56:23,292
Why is it unopened?

799
00:56:23,292 --> 00:56:24,542
What?

800
00:56:26,016 --> 00:56:27,941
Oh, that?

801
00:56:27,941 --> 00:56:30,068
It's a rare Superman collectible.

802
00:56:30,068 --> 00:56:32,734
I didn't open it in case it gets damaged.

803
00:56:33,470 --> 00:56:34,641
Want to see it?

804
00:56:34,641 --> 00:56:35,721
No, it's okay.

805
00:56:35,721 --> 00:56:37,328
If you want to see...

806
00:56:37,328 --> 00:56:39,633
No, I'm scared I might break it.

807
00:56:39,633 --> 00:56:43,098
- It's really fine.
- Come to think of it...

808
00:56:43,098 --> 00:56:45,107
you're kind of like Superman.

809
00:56:45,107 --> 00:56:46,728
Me?

810
00:56:46,728 --> 00:56:51,679
Superman wears glasses, puts on a suit,
goes to work,

811
00:56:51,679 --> 00:56:53,517
all serious and proper.

812
00:56:53,517 --> 00:56:55,317
But when he takes them off,

813
00:56:55,317 --> 00:56:57,170
no one recognizes him.

814
00:56:57,170 --> 00:56:59,933
That's how you felt at first.

815
00:56:59,933 --> 00:57:02,644
Serious. Kind of intimidating.

816
00:57:02,644 --> 00:57:04,091
Really?

817
00:57:04,091 --> 00:57:06,882
But on the train,
you took your glasses off and smiled...

818
00:57:06,882 --> 00:57:09,368
and you felt completely different.

819
00:57:11,849 --> 00:57:13,250
Noona.

820
00:57:13,250 --> 00:57:14,623
Then I'll just...

821
00:57:14,623 --> 00:57:16,723
throw out all my glasses.

822
00:57:18,083 --> 00:57:19,208
No.

823
00:57:19,208 --> 00:57:21,533
That's not what I meant. It's the contrast.

824
00:57:21,533 --> 00:57:23,391
You need the glasses at work.

825
00:57:23,391 --> 00:57:25,651
With glasses, you're Kent Clark.

826
00:57:25,651 --> 00:57:27,449
Without them, you're Superman.

827
00:57:27,449 --> 00:57:29,795
So basically... I'm dating Superman.

828
00:57:29,795 --> 00:57:31,380
His name isn't Kent Clark.

829
00:57:31,380 --> 00:57:34,011
It's Clark Kent.

830
00:57:34,011 --> 00:57:36,466
- No, it's Kent Clark.
- It's Clark Kent.

831
00:57:36,466 --> 00:57:37,852
I literally bought this, you know.

832
00:57:37,852 --> 00:57:40,159
Come on, Soon Rok.

833
00:57:40,159 --> 00:57:41,941
It's Kent Clark.

834
00:57:41,941 --> 00:57:43,731
- Want to bet?
- Whatever.

835
00:57:43,731 --> 00:57:46,309
Fine. Let's do it.

836
00:57:46,309 --> 00:57:48,581
- No holding back.
- Of course.

837
00:57:48,581 --> 00:57:50,313
Okay.

838
00:57:50,313 --> 00:57:51,987
Come on.

839
00:57:52,851 --> 00:57:54,215
See?

840
00:57:54,215 --> 00:57:56,822
Clark Kent.

841
00:57:56,822 --> 00:57:58,473
I was right.

842
00:57:58,473 --> 00:58:00,307
Come here.

843
00:58:00,307 --> 00:58:02,025
A bet's a bet.

844
00:58:02,025 --> 00:58:04,040
Yeah, but...

845
00:58:04,818 --> 00:58:06,944
Forehead.

846
00:58:23,407 --> 00:58:25,541
That was cute.

847
00:58:30,036 --> 00:58:32,124
Did that hurt?

848
00:58:33,291 --> 00:58:34,481
It did, right?

849
00:58:34,481 --> 00:58:36,333
- Hit me back.
- No.

850
00:58:36,333 --> 00:58:37,392
Go ahead.

851
00:58:37,392 --> 00:58:39,285
- No.
- It's fine, hit me.

852
00:58:39,285 --> 00:58:42,151
- It's a bet.
- Fine, go on.

853
00:58:44,569 --> 00:58:45,970
Hit...

854
00:58:50,244 --> 00:58:51,351
Let's just play the game.

855
00:58:51,351 --> 00:58:53,224
- Okay, but...
- Just one round.

856
00:58:53,224 --> 00:58:55,430
- That was too hard...
- That game from last time, huh?

857
00:58:56,904 --> 00:58:57,968
Noona,

858
00:58:57,968 --> 00:58:59,574
let's drop that now.

859
00:58:59,574 --> 00:59:00,662
Let's go watch a movie.

860
00:59:00,662 --> 00:59:02,025
A movie?

861
00:59:02,025 --> 00:59:03,790
You booked tickets?

862
00:59:03,790 --> 00:59:06,763
You thought we'd just play games all night?

863
00:59:06,763 --> 00:59:08,594
Come on, let's go.

864
00:59:08,594 --> 00:59:10,956
- Okay.
- Let's go.

865
00:59:17,052 --> 00:59:19,517
Since you like Superman,

866
00:59:19,517 --> 00:59:21,917
I got the original version.

867
00:59:21,917 --> 00:59:22,975
Really?

868
00:59:22,975 --> 00:59:24,801
Where's it playing?

869
00:59:36,211 --> 00:59:38,123
Let's see.

870
00:59:38,123 --> 00:59:41,223
Row J, seats 6 and 7.

871
00:59:43,542 --> 00:59:46,042
This is a theater?

872
00:59:46,042 --> 00:59:47,193
Here it is.

873
00:59:47,193 --> 00:59:50,013
Noona, over here.

874
00:59:50,013 --> 00:59:52,813
So this is how you hang out at home.

875
00:59:53,600 --> 00:59:56,608
- This is a lot.
- Just let him do his thing.

876
00:59:56,608 --> 00:59:58,614
He's Gen Z, after all.

877
01:00:02,234 --> 01:00:05,088
<i>Noona, come this way.</i>

878
01:00:05,088 --> 01:00:07,178
<i>But...</i>

879
01:00:07,178 --> 01:00:10,154
<i>there's no one here.</i>

880
01:00:10,977 --> 01:00:13,496
<i>I rented it out.</i>

881
01:00:13,496 --> 01:00:15,083
<i>This whole place?</i>

882
01:00:15,083 --> 01:00:16,623
<i>For me,</i>

883
01:00:16,623 --> 01:00:19,263
<i>renting out a theater</i>

884
01:00:19,263 --> 01:00:21,436
<i>is nothing.</i>

885
01:00:22,909 --> 01:00:25,812
<i>What is this, some chaebol heir concept?</i>

886
01:00:26,664 --> 01:00:29,266
<i>And you'd be the broke writer.</i>

887
01:00:30,429 --> 01:00:34,723
<i>And here I am,
renting out a whole theater for you...</i>

888
01:00:38,470 --> 01:00:40,498
<i>How ridiculous.</i>

889
01:00:42,958 --> 01:00:44,932
<i>Seriously...</i>

890
01:00:46,794 --> 01:00:50,588
<i>what about you made me like this?</i>

891
01:00:52,700 --> 01:00:56,153
<i>Must be my good looks, right?</i>

892
01:00:56,153 --> 01:00:58,378
<i>Not wrong, though.</i>

893
01:01:05,503 --> 01:01:08,023
Looks like the ice cream's here.

894
01:01:12,377 --> 01:01:14,199
Ice cream?

895
01:01:18,036 --> 01:01:19,686
That's a lot.

896
01:01:19,686 --> 01:01:21,263
All different flavors.

897
01:01:21,263 --> 01:01:22,538
Twelve kinds.

898
01:01:22,538 --> 01:01:24,977
Isn't this a bit much?

899
01:01:24,977 --> 01:01:27,913
I ordered extra since you're here.

900
01:01:27,913 --> 01:01:29,440
Just in case it wasn't enough.

901
01:01:29,440 --> 01:01:32,424
I just think you spent too much.

902
01:01:32,424 --> 01:01:35,106
Come on, eat before it melts.

903
01:01:36,791 --> 01:01:39,918
This isn't the kind of ice cream
you get every day.

904
01:01:40,921 --> 01:01:42,800
Especially

905
01:01:43,588 --> 01:01:46,321
out here in the mountains.

906
01:01:54,947 --> 01:01:57,288
<i>The smell might draw wolves.</i>

907
01:01:57,288 --> 01:01:59,516
<i>Better finish it all.</i>

908
01:02:04,024 --> 01:02:05,984
<i>Soon Rok.</i>

909
01:02:05,984 --> 01:02:07,728
<i>Being with you,</i>

910
01:02:07,728 --> 01:02:10,090
<i>I lose track of time.</i>

911
01:02:17,191 --> 01:02:18,777
<i>Did you hear that?</i>

912
01:02:20,721 --> 01:02:23,055
<i>- I think it came from over there.
- Right.</i>

913
01:02:41,573 --> 01:02:42,928
Who would've thought?

914
01:02:42,928 --> 01:02:46,003
PD Shin had this side to him.

915
01:02:46,003 --> 01:02:47,709
That's kind of cute.

916
01:02:53,011 --> 01:02:55,024
Soon Rok.

917
01:02:56,398 --> 01:02:58,458
Where'd he go?

918
01:03:05,908 --> 01:03:07,509
Who is it?

919
01:03:07,509 --> 01:03:09,544
Delivery.

920
01:03:11,852 --> 01:03:13,874
Soon Rok?

921
01:03:14,749 --> 01:03:16,725
Is that you?

922
01:03:18,266 --> 01:03:19,487
What?

923
01:03:19,487 --> 01:03:21,017
Why are you ringing the bell?

924
01:03:21,017 --> 01:03:22,757
Soon Rok?

925
01:03:22,757 --> 01:03:25,124
What are you talking about?

926
01:03:25,124 --> 01:03:26,895
I'm here

927
01:03:26,895 --> 01:03:29,175
<i>to deliver waffles.</i>

928
01:03:29,175 --> 01:03:31,646
<i>Now you're a delivery guy?</i>

929
01:03:31,646 --> 01:03:35,419
<i>Wouldn't waffles go well
with the leftover ice cream?</i>

930
01:03:36,305 --> 01:03:37,344
<i>Good idea.</i>

931
01:03:37,344 --> 01:03:39,615
<i>Thanks for the delivery.</i>

932
01:03:39,615 --> 01:03:42,475
<i>So how should I pay?</i>

933
01:03:42,475 --> 01:03:44,327
<i>A kiss?</i>

934
01:03:56,745 --> 01:03:58,140
What?

935
01:03:58,140 --> 01:04:01,353
You're seriously addicted to roleplay.

936
01:04:01,353 --> 01:04:03,405
You should've been the writer, not me.

937
01:04:03,405 --> 01:04:05,302
One second.

938
01:04:05,302 --> 01:04:06,946
Thanks.

939
01:04:11,108 --> 01:04:12,870
I'm sorry, Master.

940
01:04:14,028 --> 01:04:17,446
I dozed off and didn't realize you called.

941
01:04:17,446 --> 01:04:19,872
<i>When did I call you?</i>

942
01:04:19,872 --> 01:04:21,950
<i>I didn't ask for you.</i>

943
01:04:21,950 --> 01:04:24,563
No, you did.

944
01:04:28,239 --> 01:04:32,116
I've fully restored your stamina and mana.

945
01:04:35,483 --> 01:04:37,806
This looks good.

946
01:04:37,806 --> 01:04:40,912
I'm already full, but let's just dig in.

947
01:04:41,648 --> 01:04:43,419
One second.

948
01:04:53,399 --> 01:04:55,124
[Tongue Cell]

949
01:04:55,124 --> 01:04:56,577
Don't be nervous.

950
01:04:56,577 --> 01:04:59,357
Yeah, I'm always ready!

951
01:05:04,372 --> 01:05:05,773
No need to stress.

952
01:05:05,773 --> 01:05:07,756
It's not your first time.

953
01:05:09,083 --> 01:05:10,128
Of course!

954
01:05:10,128 --> 01:05:13,494
But this mission could go long tonight.

955
01:05:13,494 --> 01:05:15,939
Kissing is always ready.

956
01:05:15,939 --> 01:05:17,252
The tricky part is...

957
01:05:18,763 --> 01:05:21,490
timing it right.

958
01:05:23,762 --> 01:05:26,171
You should've called first.

959
01:05:26,963 --> 01:05:29,749
I'll head over now. I'll be there soon.

960
01:05:31,375 --> 01:05:33,121
I'm nearby.

961
01:05:33,121 --> 01:05:34,581
The book cafe.

962
01:05:35,213 --> 01:05:36,333
Okay,

963
01:05:36,333 --> 01:05:38,042
I'll be right there.

964
01:05:39,588 --> 01:05:40,988
Where are you going?

965
01:05:40,988 --> 01:05:45,333
Sorry. My parents just got home.

966
01:05:45,333 --> 01:05:46,611
Right now?

967
01:05:46,611 --> 01:05:50,224
They showed up out of nowhere.
They're dropping off kimchi.

968
01:05:51,088 --> 01:05:53,164
I should go.

969
01:06:02,739 --> 01:06:04,746
There's my dad's car.

970
01:06:06,552 --> 01:06:08,577
You should go now.

971
01:06:08,577 --> 01:06:10,290
Okay.

972
01:06:15,443 --> 01:06:17,161
Get home safe.

973
01:06:17,161 --> 01:06:18,983
I'll text you.

974
01:06:20,388 --> 01:06:22,401
- Bye.
- Bye.

975
01:06:27,638 --> 01:06:29,345
Bye.

976
01:06:38,650 --> 01:06:40,306
Bye.

977
01:06:40,306 --> 01:06:42,112
See you tomorrow.

978
01:07:15,885 --> 01:07:18,539
<i>She's gone now.</i>

979
01:07:18,539 --> 01:07:21,314
<i>I wanted to hang out all night.</i>

980
01:07:49,380 --> 01:07:50,906
[Writer Kim]

981
01:07:55,250 --> 01:07:56,531
Noona?

982
01:07:56,531 --> 01:07:58,125
<i>What are you doing? Sleeping?</i>

983
01:07:58,125 --> 01:07:59,154
No.

984
01:07:59,154 --> 01:08:03,540
My parents just dropped off
the kimchi and left.

985
01:08:06,429 --> 01:08:08,306
Want to come over?

986
01:08:10,917 --> 01:08:12,528
Or we can just meet tomorrow if you're tired.

987
01:08:12,528 --> 01:08:14,163
I'll come now.

988
01:08:14,163 --> 01:08:15,711
I'll be there soon.

989
01:08:53,167 --> 01:08:56,866
So then I realized I forgot the carrots.

990
01:08:56,866 --> 01:08:58,177
So I called my mom

991
01:08:58,177 --> 01:09:00,824
and asked if we could just skip them,

992
01:09:00,824 --> 01:09:03,375
but she said I had to get them no matter what.

993
01:09:03,375 --> 01:09:04,449
So what could I do?

994
01:09:04,449 --> 01:09:06,387
The moment she finishes her sentence,

995
01:09:06,387 --> 01:09:09,053
you jump in.

996
01:09:09,053 --> 01:09:11,351
And then the mart was closing.

997
01:09:11,351 --> 01:09:12,895
They wouldn't let me in,

998
01:09:12,895 --> 01:09:16,087
so I kept begging them, like, "I'm so sorry..."

999
01:09:16,087 --> 01:09:18,965
The problem is, that's still one sentence.

1000
01:09:18,965 --> 01:09:21,222
So I rushed in, apologizing,

1001
01:09:21,222 --> 01:09:22,917
grabbed the carrots real quick...

1002
01:09:22,917 --> 01:09:24,603
This won't work. You have to cut her off.

1003
01:09:24,603 --> 01:09:27,462
There's no choice but to interrupt.

1004
01:09:27,462 --> 01:09:30,669
What if we cut in with an emergency kiss?

1005
01:09:30,669 --> 01:09:32,417
And then my mom was already buying carrots.

1006
01:09:32,417 --> 01:09:33,948
She literally told me to get them...

1007
01:09:33,948 --> 01:09:35,807
No, that's risky.

1008
01:09:35,807 --> 01:09:37,428
She's too far away.

1009
01:09:37,428 --> 01:09:40,875
You might knock over the wine glass.

1010
01:09:40,875 --> 01:09:41,990
You know what?

1011
01:09:41,990 --> 01:09:43,017
What?

1012
01:09:43,017 --> 01:09:46,010
Most of what I do is a gamble.

1013
01:09:53,220 --> 01:09:55,118
Tasting if something's salty or not...

1014
01:09:55,118 --> 01:09:56,693
Damn, that's salty!

1015
01:09:58,295 --> 01:10:02,207
Even checking battery levels is a gamble.

1016
01:10:02,207 --> 01:10:03,598
It was so ridiculous.

1017
01:10:03,598 --> 01:10:05,884
So I told my mom...

1018
01:10:07,709 --> 01:10:10,201
I'm scared of risks,

1019
01:10:10,201 --> 01:10:14,154
but it's something only I can do!

1020
01:11:19,916 --> 01:11:22,779
<i>I wonder how many people</i>

1021
01:11:22,779 --> 01:11:25,633
<i>know who Soon Rok really is.</i>

1022
01:12:00,375 --> 01:12:01,824
<i>You said you wanted to visit Kyoto.</i>

1023
01:12:01,824 --> 01:12:03,944
<i>Did you see that? Who just walked by?</i>

1024
01:12:03,944 --> 01:12:04,803
<i>Hello? Noona?</i>

1025
01:12:04,803 --> 01:12:07,721
<i>Maybe we should tell the editor.</i>

1026
01:12:07,721 --> 01:12:10,285
<i>Soon Rok's principles are who he is.</i>

1027
01:12:10,285 --> 01:12:12,383
<i>Such a cute face!</i>

1028
01:12:12,383 --> 01:12:14,917
<i>And skin as white as snow...</i>

1029
01:12:14,917 --> 01:12:16,918
<i>I don't agree!</i>

1030
01:12:16,918 --> 01:12:17,978
<i>Let go!</i>

1031
01:12:17,978 --> 01:12:19,145
<i>Watch out!</i>

1032
01:12:19,145 --> 01:12:21,125
<i>I can wait.</i>

1033
01:12:21,125 --> 01:12:24,030
<i>Love is always surprising</i>

1034
01:12:24,030 --> 01:12:28,263
<i>because no two loves are ever the same.</i>
